---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="CodeVault Privacy Policy - How we handle your data">
  <section class="py-24 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900 to-slate-950">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">Last updated: December 2024</p>

      <div class="prose prose-slate prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          CodeVault ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our services.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Core Privacy Principle</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Your code never leaves your infrastructure.</strong> CodeVault is deployed on-premise or in your private cloud. All AI processing happens locally on your servers. We do not have access to your source code, prompts, or AI-generated responses.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Name, email address, company name when you contact us or request a demo</li>
          <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Login credentials for accessing our support portal</li>
          <li><strong>Communication Data:</strong> Messages, feedback, and support requests you send us</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Your source code</li>
          <li>AI prompts or queries</li>
          <li>AI-generated responses</li>
          <li>Your codebase contents</li>
          <li>Any data processed by your CodeVault deployment</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide deployment and support services</li>
          <li>Respond to your inquiries and requests</li>
          <li>Send important updates about your service</li>
          <li>Improve our products and services</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information. Your CodeVault deployment is entirely under your control, running on your infrastructure with your security policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your contact and account information for as long as necessary to provide our services. You may request deletion of your personal data at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We may use third-party services for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email communication</li>
          <li>Customer support</li>
          <li>Analytics on our marketing website</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These services do not have access to your CodeVault deployment or any data processed by it.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal data</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
          <li>Data portability</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@codevault.dev
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
